{"title":"Surly’s Big Easy Gets Updates for 2024","link":"https://theradavist.com/surly-big-easy-updates-2024/","date":1711633029000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/20240209_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_109.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240209_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_109.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240209_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_109.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240209_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_109.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240209_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_109.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Morgan reviewed the <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/review-surly-big-easy-electric-cargo-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">Big Easy a few years ago</a> and in that time, the special minds at Surly have been working on some updates…<span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/20240208_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_007.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240208_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_007.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240208_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_007.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240208_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_007.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240208_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_007.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Most notably, the Big Easy got a new motor by Bosch. It’s more powerful than ever now. The rear deck got larger, there’s a lower stand over for riders, a damping headset, more cargo and bottle boses, and the list goes on!</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/20240210_SUR_BigEasy2_Vanity_04.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240210_SUR_BigEasy2_Vanity_04.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240210_SUR_BigEasy2_Vanity_04.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240210_SUR_BigEasy2_Vanity_04.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240210_SUR_BigEasy2_Vanity_04.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/20240209_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_095.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240209_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_095.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240209_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_095.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240209_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_095.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/03/20240209_SUR_BigEasy2_Lifestyle_Atlanta_095.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>The new Big Easy updates include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Full component set selected for the demands of heavy cargo hauling</li>\n<li>Expanded rider fit per size to improve bike sharing among different-sized riders</li>\n<li>The most powerful Bosch electric bike motor for elevated performance</li>\n<li>The Surly dual-leg kickstand for unmatched stability when loading and unloading cargo</li>\n<li>Rear deck now accommodates two child seats – no adapter needed (Thule Yepp Nexxt Maxi and Burley Dash)</li>\n<li>Lower stand over height for improved stability when stopping, mounting, and dismounting</li>\n<li>Surly Sunrise handlebars that give riders leverage to control heavy loads</li>\n<li>Simplified Big Dummy bags made with BlueSign-approved fabrics</li>\n<li>Damping headset for smooth and stable handling under heavy loads</li>\n</ul>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://surlybikes.com/bikes/big_easy\" target=\"_blank\">Surly</a>.</p>\n<p><em>If you haven’t <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/review-surly-big-easy-electric-cargo-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">read Morgan’s review</a>, you should check it out!</em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/surly-big-easy-updates-2024/\">Surly’s Big Easy Gets Updates for 2024</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"2495d07e1fed4290e4cbda963432f698a3ed783f48db73bf7243e454935bdb30","category":"Cycling"}